<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="working-with-clients-on-music">Working With Clients on Music</h2>

<p>Music is personal. That&#8217;s what makes it so powerful &#8212; and that&#8217;s why DJ Misha treats every client conversation about music as one of the most important parts of the planning process.</p>

<p>The process typically starts with a detailed discussion about the event: What&#8217;s the energy you&#8217;re going for? Are there specific songs or genres that feel essential? Are there artists or sounds you absolutely want to avoid? What&#8217;s the demographic of the crowd &#8212; and what are they expecting? These questions aren&#8217;t a formality. They&#8217;re the raw material that DJ Misha uses to build a custom musical roadmap for your event.</p>

<p>From there, DJ Misha takes that input and translates it into a curated direction &#8212; not a rigid track list, but a musical framework that honors your vision while leaving room for the organic energy of the evening. Because here&#8217;s the thing: a crowd at 9pm is not the same crowd at 11pm. Reading that shift in real time &#8212; and adjusting the music accordingly &#8212; is where experience makes all the difference.</p>

<p>You know your guests, your occasion, and what feels right for the moment. DJ Misha brings the musical knowledge, the music collection, and the craft to bring that vision to life on the dance floor. It&#8217;s a collaboration &#8212; and the result is a set that feels both intentional and spontaneous, both personal and universally fun.</p>

